### Sequential API

The Sequential API is the simplest way to build models, using a single
straightforward stack of layers.

#### Figure 3.4 — Sequential model diagram
<p align="left"><img src="./figure/figure3.4.png" width="60%"></p>

---

### Functional API

The Functional API extends flexibility by allowing multi–input, multi–output,
branched, and shared–layer networks—used widely in modern architectures such
as ResNet and Inception.

#### Figure 3.5 — Functional API model flow
<p align="left"><img src="./figure/figure3.5.png" width="60%"></p>

---

### Sub-classing API

The Sub-classing API provides full control by defining models as custom Python
classes with a custom forward pass, ideal for research or specialized network
designs.

